RF Model Performances

The testing set was split based on random unique combinations of date and transect without replacement into approximately 0.75:0.25 training:testing set split (i.e., 300:100 records).

The testing set was used as a hold-out set and used only to evaluate final trained models. The testing set was subset based on random unique combinations of three sampling dates and two transects without replacement. This method was adopted to ensure that the testing and training samples were not too similar because of spatial autocorrelation, which would result if a simple random splitting was done. Furthermore, to check for possible bias that may result from training:testing set split, we randomly generated 30 unique training-testing set splits and trained 30 models based on the 30 training sets and tested the model performance on their respective testing sets.
